      "content": "The rule of law demands that all individuals, regardless of their origin, must abide by the established legal framework of the nation they enter. When immigration laws are systematically ignored, it signals that the law is optional for some, which fundamentally erodes the concept of a shared social contract. If the government cannot enforce its own foundational laws, its legitimacy as a governing body collapses, creating a state of legal chaos. Therefore, enforcement is a moral imperative to uphold the very structure of civil society.",
