      "content": "The argument that law should not supersede human rights is a dangerous fallacy when applied to national borders. A nation's primary, non-negotiable duty is to protect its existing citizens and maintain its legal order, which is the prerequisite for any human rights to be guaranteed. Humanitarian concerns must be addressed through established legal channels, such as asylum processes, not by creating a loophole in the sovereign's right to control entry. Allowing lawlessness in the name of sentimentality ultimately harms the very people the opposition claims to protect.",
